The process has started to amend the country's identity laws to possibly include a third gender. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports. #eNCA #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - South Africa's Constitution is often referred to as one of the most progressive in the world. It was the first on the African Continent to legalise same-sex marriages. Now, the process has started to amend the country's identity laws to possibly include a third gender. Comments and proposals have been submitted to Home Affairs by interested parties. Watch the video above for more on this story.